subsection.p:
\boxed{ \omega=e^{2\pi i/n} }
Then the nth roots of unity are
\boxed{ 1,\omega,\omega^2,\ldots,\omega^{n-1}. }
Also,
\boxed{ \omega^n=1. }

The map
z\mapsto z^n
does two things:
\boxed{ \text{length } r \mapsto r^n }
\boxed{ \text{angle } \theta \mapsto n\theta. }

Taking nth roots reverses those operations:
\boxed{ \text{length } R \mapsto R^{1/n} }
\boxed{ \text{angle } \Theta \mapsto \frac{\Theta+2\pi k}{n}. }
